{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc37a72f8-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3524"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3524"},"text":"§ 3524.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Discontinuance for unsatisfactory progress","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall discontinue the educational assistance allowance on behalf of an eligible person if, at any time, the Secretary finds that according to the regularly prescribed standards and practices of the educational institution such person is attending, the person’s attendance, conduct, or progress is unsatisfactory. The Secretary may renew the payment of the educational assistance allowance only if the Secretary finds that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc37a72f9-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3524/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the eligible person will be resuming enrollment at the same educational institution in the same program of education and the educational institution has both approved such eligible person’s reenrollment and certified it to the Department of Veterans Affairs; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc37a72fa-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3524/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a proposed change of either educational institution or program of education by the eligible person—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc37a72fb-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3524/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the cause of the unsatisfactory attendance, conduct, or progress has been removed;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc37a72fc-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3524/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the program proposed to be pursued is suitable to the eligible person’s aptitudes, interests, and abilities; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc37a72fd-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3524/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" if a proposed change of program is involved, the change meets the requirements for approval under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s3691"},"text":"section 3691 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc37a72fe-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/857"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–857","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1197"},"text":"72 Stat. 1197","children":[],"tail":", § 1724; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/502/tIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–502, title III","children":[],"tail":", §§ 307, 310(15), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2390"},"text":"90 Stat. 2390","children":[],"tail":", 2392; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/202/tIII/s305/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–202, title III, § 305(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-11-23"},"text":"Nov. 23, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1443"},"text":"91 Stat. 1443","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466/tIII/s328"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–466, title III, § 328","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2197"},"text":"94 Stat. 2197","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/237/tIV"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–237, title IV","children":[],"tail":", §§ 411(b), 412(b), 423(b)(1)(A), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2084"},"text":"103 Stat. 2084","children":[],"tail":", 2085, 2092; renumbered § 3524 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/406"},"text":"105 Stat. 406","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc37a72ff-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc37a7300-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc37a7301-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1724"},"text":"section 1724 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “3691” for “1791”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/237/s423/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–237, § 423(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/237/s412/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–237, § 412(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “attendance, conduct,” for “conduct”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (1), (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/237/s411/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–237, § 411(b)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (1) and (2) and struck out former pars. (1) and (2) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) the cause of the unsatisfactory conduct or progress of the eligible person has been removed; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) the program which the eligible person now proposes to pursue (whether the same or revised) is suitable to the person’s aptitudes, interests, and abilities.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–466","children":[],"tail":" struck out provisions relating to the conditions upon which an eligible person’s progress would be considered unsatisfactory."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1977—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/202"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–202","children":[],"tail":" inserted provisions authorizing the Administrator to determine the veteran’s progress to be satisfactory even though the veteran will graduate within a length of time exceeding the approved length if the additional length of time is reasonable in accordance with regulations."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/502/s310/15"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–502, § 310(15)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “such person is attending” for “he is attending”, “the Administrator finds that” for “he finds that”, and “the person’s” for “his” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/502/s307"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–502, § 307","children":[],"tail":", inserted provision specifying progress as unsatisfactory when the veteran will not be able to graduate within the approved length of the course."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc37a7302-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idc37a7303-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–466","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1980","children":[],"tail":", except as otherwise specifically provided, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466/s802/c"},"text":"section 802(c) of Pub. L. 96–466","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s3452"},"text":"section 3452 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idc37a7304-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1977 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/202"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–202","children":[],"tail":" effective first day of first month beginning 60 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-11-23"},"text":"Nov. 23, 1977","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/202/s501"},"text":"section 501 of Pub. L. 95–202","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idc37a7305-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1976 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by sections 307 and 310(15) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/502"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–502","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-12-01"},"text":"Dec. 1, 1976","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1976","children":[],"tail":", respectively, see section 703(b), (c) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/502"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–502","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s3693"},"text":"section 3693 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idc37a7306-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Suspension of Implementation of 1976 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For provisions directing the Administrator to suspend the implementation of the amendment to this section by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/502/s307"},"text":"section 307 of Pub. L. 94–502","children":[],"tail":" in the case of any accredited educational institution which submits to the Administrator its course catalog or bulletin and a certification that the policies and regulations described in cls. (6) and (7) of section 1776(b) [now 3676(b)(6) and (7)] of this title are being enforced by such institution, unless the Administrator finds that the catalog or bulletin fails to state fully and clearly the policies and regulations, and for that suspension to continue until the Administrator submits the report required under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/202/s305/b/2"},"text":"section 305(b)(2) of Pub. L. 95–202","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/202/s305/b/4/A"},"text":"section 305(b)(4)(A) of Pub. L. 95–202","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s3474"},"text":"section 3474 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
